tweet: 6/ As regards my confidence in #BTC hitting those projected prices at cycle peak ($175K-$425K) by year end, the On-chain Peaking Indicator is reflective of that.  Thanks for riding with me on this exciting journey in learning & investing in #BTC!

name: Allen Au ğŸ§¢
tweet: 4/ The current #BTC cycle peak dates are determined based on duration from mid-cycle correction to cycle peak & 60D VVOL in past cycles. They've been fairly accurate in predicting the cycle peak dates. If this doesn't happen, I will use other means to determine cycle peak timing.

name: Allen Au ğŸ§¢
tweet: 3/ As for the BLX Model, the peak is determined to be at the confluence of various trend lines, arcs & trend angle trend line. If the monthly closing #BTC price were to fall out of the arc/parabola, the model will be redrawn to determine the new cycle peak price and date.

name: Allen Au ğŸ§¢
tweet: 2/ #BTC is determined to be peaking when its price touches the top trend line of Top Cap & one of the fib lines of Fib Multipliers.   The Top Cap price & Fib prices are reported daily so you can gauge BTC's price if the cycle peak were to happen on the day the Dash Board is out.

name: Allen Au ğŸ§¢
tweet: Q&A: Do the models break if #BTC doesn't peak at the projected dates?   1/ Yes & no. Yes in that BTC doesn't peak as expected. But the Top Cap, Fib Multipliers & BLX models are based on BTC's price & they don't lose their predictive ability. It's the timing that is off.
